This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and optimization methods for training models on distributed edge devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with issues related to communication and system configurations of edge devices, which could fall under categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of real-world datasets, which could suggest a category such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for federated learning, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
